          <title>A Critical Microsoft Exchange Server Flaw Remains Unpatched: A Serious Security Concern</title>
          <description><![CDATA[A critical security vulnerability in Microsoft Exchange servers has been largely unpatched, despite a fix being issued four years ago. This flaw may have aided the hacking group Salt Typhoon, and experts are urging security teams to take action to secure their networks.]]></description>
